240 grams British Beef Mince
80 grams Sliced Mushrooms
1 sachet(s) Thai Style Spice Mix
120 grams Coleslaw Mix
125 grams Egg Noodle Nest
75 grams Bulgogi Sauce
15 milliliter(s) Soy Sauce
5 grams Roasted White Sesame Seeds
2 tbsp Tomato Ketchup

Boil a full kettle.
Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on high heat.
Once hot, fry the beef mince, mushrooms, Thai style spice mix (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and coleslaw mix, 5-6 mins.
Break up the mince as it cooks.

Meanwhile, pour the hot water into a saucepan with 1/4 salt.
Boil the noodles, 3-4 mins.
Once cooked, drain and run under cold water.
Drain the fat from the beef.
Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Stir in the bulgogi, soy and ketchup (see pantry).
Add the noodles. Toss to coat.
Heat up, 1-2 mins.
Taste and season if needed. Add a splash of water if needed.

Share your bulgogi noodles between the serving bowls.
Sprinkle over the sesame seeds.
Enjoy!